    "methodSteps": [
        "Firstly chop the {onion} and fry in half the {oil} for 5 minutes on a medium heat until softened/carmelised, stirring every 30s.",
        "Next create a base mixture by blending the fried {onion} with the {yog}, {garlic}, {ginger}, half the {cream}, and quater of the {tomatos} until smooth.",
        "Now add the base mixture into a pan (large enough to hold the finished dish) with the remaining {oil} and {tomatos}, cook on the hob on a medium heat for 2 minutes then decrease the heat to low.",
        "Whilst the base mixture simmers, grind the {coriander}, {cumin}, {blackCumin}, {cloves}, {fenugreek}, {pepper}, {cardamoms}, {poppy}, {bay} and {cinamon} together using a pestle and mortar or an electric spice (or coffee) grinder",
        "Also whilst the base mixture simmers, chop the {meat} into small cube shaped pieces (smaller pieces absorb more flavour).",
        "Cook the {meat} in a seperate pan with the lid on, on a low heat with 50ml of cold water, 1 tsp of the ground spice mixture and half the {salt} for 20 minutes.",
        "Once the base mixture has simmered for at least 15 minutes, add the ground spice mix to the base with a splash of cold water to prevent the spices from burning. Mix well and leave to simmer on a low heat for 15 minutes.",
        "Now add the {turmeric}, the remaining {salt} and all the {chilliePowder} with another splash of water and simmer for a further 10 minutes.",
        "Once the 10 minutes has passed, add the {meat} into the pan with the remaining {cream} and cook for at least 15 minutes on a low heat, stirring every few minutes.",
        "Next chop the {chillies} and add to the pan, increase the heat to high and stir the curry well.",
        "Heat the {naan} as described on the packet.",
        "Finally, add the {freshCoriander} and {kewra} to the curry and stir well for 30s. Serve the curry then garnish it with {garam}, serve the {naan} on a seperate plate.",
        "Enjoy!"
    ]

        }